<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-095-074 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 278 511</DOCID><JOURNAL>The OSINetter Newsletter  August 1991 v6 n8 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Architecture Technology Corp. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Europe's largest private ISDN network goes into operation.andO;(Northern Telecom Europe Ltd. provides Integrated Services DigitalNetwork)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Northern Telecom Europe Ltd. (Services).andO;Topic:     ISDNEuropePersonal Communications NetworksPrivate Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>EUROPE'S LARGEST PRIVATE ISDN NETWORK GOES INTO OPERATIONandM;Northern Telecom announced that Europe's largest private European ISDNnetwork went into operation on time in Germany at BASF AG in Ludwigshafen.andO;Approximately 28,000 extensions within the chemical company comprise aMeridian 1 ISDN network handling more than 250,000 calls each day.andM;It took approximately one year of planning and preparation in order toreplace the old BASF network--which was based on hybrid technology--with themodern digital Meridian 1 network.andP;  Now, as a result, BASF has the largestand most modern ISDN network in Europe, linking several company locations.andO;Expansion beyond the German borders is now being considered.andM;In the Northern Telecom system, user facilities such as call diversion,automatic ringback, voice message storage, and an integrated automatic calldistribution system are available over the entire network to all users.andM;Information:  Ian Morris, Northern Telecom Europe Limited, Saint Cloud Way,Maidenhead, Bershire SL6 8XB, England, telephone 44 753 813190, Fax 44 753813496; Linda Hensen, Northern Telecom Inc., 200 Athens Way, Nashville, TN37228, (615) 734-4251.andO;</TEXT></DOC>